id: pm-yjim
title: "GH-473: pm install prints a post-install verification summary"
description: "Dogfood GH-473: after pm install <package>, agents must run pm package doctor to confirm the install worked; a brief inline verification summary saves an invocation. Duplicate check: searched post-install verification summary — pm-b3e9 covers PRE-install owning-package hints; no overlap."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: agent-experience,gh-issue,packages,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:09:23.206Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T07:08:21.271Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T07:08:19.744Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "pm install output ends with a verification summary (activation status, registered commands/types, health ok/degraded) equivalent to a light package-doctor pass; failures keep the existing per-target failure rows; covered by specs"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Added compact post-install verification covering activation, registrations, target root, and blocking health."
expected_result: Agents can confirm install success without a separate doctor invocation.
actual_result: Single and multi-package install results include coherent light verification and failure counts.
